Airlink plans to start a daily return flight between the two cities on February 6 using one of its 20 Embraer 135 37-seat jets. This is an exciting development on our domestic route network which we believe will be popular with both business and leisure travelers said Airlink marketing and sales manager Karin Murray.Flights will leave Pietermaritzburg at 7am and land in Cape Town at 9.10am and depart from Cape Town at 5.35pm and arrive in Pietermartizburg at 7.30pm.TMG Digital/Cape Newsroom